main event: A housewife and her family reported seeing two strange objects with multiple lights over Lake Jacomo in Lees Summit, Missouri on February 14, 1967.
interesting points: One of the objects was described as round with 5 white lights, while the other was round with a red light, flashing green and blue lights, and a tail.
The objects were seen circling each other at close range, with one of the objects almost covered by a halo.
The objects were seen by 10 people, including the housewife, her 14-year-old son, two other sons ages 12 and 13, and two male neighbors ages 16 and 15.
The housewife stated she has 20/20 vision and does not wear glasses, and her husband is a fireman.
The Air Force contacted a C-124 aircraft in the area, but the pilot reported no visual contact with the objects.
sighted object: two round objects with multiple lights, one with a tail
witnesses: a housewife, her 3 sons, and 2 male neighbors
